{"id":57603,"date":"2011-05-19T03:33:12","date_gmt":"2011-05-19T03:33:12","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/pullmonkey.com\/?p=57603"},"modified":"2011-05-19T03:33:12","modified_gmt":"2011-05-19T03:33:12","slug":"ubuntu-the-disk-drive-for-x-is-not-ready-yet-or-not-present","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/pullmonkey.com\/2011\/05\/19\/ubuntu-the-disk-drive-for-x-is-not-ready-yet-or-not-present\/","title":{"rendered":"Ubuntu &#8211; The disk drive for X is not ready yet or not present"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>After an Ubuntu install go wrong my laptop started coming up with this error message:<br \/>\n<strong>The disk drive for X is not ready yet or not present<\/strong><br \/>\nIn my case, the laptop was having trouble with \/dev\/sda1, my root partition.<br \/>\n<strong>The Solution:<\/strong><br \/>\nThe error message above is met with two solutions, press S to skip or M to do a manual install.  Press \"M\" for manual install.<br \/>\nOnce you are the command prompt, your drive will have been mounted as read-only, change that like this:<\/p>\n<pre>mount \/dev\/sda1 -o rw,remount<\/pre>\n<p>Now that the drive is in read-write again (test with a simple touch \/tmp\/test), continue the installation with this:<\/p>\n<pre>dpkg --configure -a<\/pre>\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>After an Ubuntu install go wrong my laptop started coming up with this error message: The disk drive for X is not ready yet or not present In my case, the laptop was having trouble with \/dev\/sda1, my root partition. The Solution: The error message above is met with two solutions, press S to skip [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[149],"tags":[173,46,172,221,175,174,150],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/pullmonkey.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/57603"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/pullmonkey.com\/wp